anced above 10 GeV relative to a background flux model. This implies that\nalternative sources such as young, nearby pulsars and supernova remnants should\ncontribute additional primary positrons within the astrophysical scenario.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 23 Oct 2014 19:36:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 2 Feb 2015 13:09:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-23"}
